# raycast-contacts

A Raycast extension that searches, creates, edits, and deletes Apple Contacts (macOS native).

## What it does

- **Search Contacts** — single command; searches all Apple Contacts via JXA (osascript)
- **Split-pane layout** — alphabetically-sectioned list on the left; rich markdown detail on the right (always visible, no toggle)
- **Detail panel** — photo, phones, emails, addresses, birthday, job title, notes; loaded on-demand per selection
- **Create contact** — `⌘N` opens `ContactForm`; writes to default address book via JXA
- **Edit contact** — `⌘E` opens `ContactForm` pre-populated; replaces phone/email and saves
- **Delete contact** — `⌃X` in action panel; shows destructive confirmation dialog, then deletes via JXA and revalidates the list
- **Actions** — Compose Email, Call, Open in Contacts, Copy phone/email/name, Refresh, Delete

## File map

```
src/
  search-contacts.tsx         command entry; wires useContacts → ContactList
  apple-contacts.ts           all JXA logic: bulk list fetch, detail fetch, create, update, delete;
                                normalizeKey / mergeContacts / deduplicateContacts (exported)
  hooks.ts                    useContacts() — useCachedPromise wrapper around fetchAppleContacts
  types.ts                    UnifiedContact, ContactField, ContactAddress
  helpers.ts                  groupByLetter (A–Z + "#"), formatBirthday ("YYYY-M-D" → "MM-DD[-YYYY]")
  components/
    ContactList.tsx           split-pane List; fetches detail on selection change via useCachedPromise
    ContactActions.tsx        ActionPanel: email/call/open/copy/refresh/delete (with confirmAlert)
    ContactForm.tsx           create & edit form (useForm from @raycast/utils)
  __tests__/
    helpers.test.ts           unit tests for groupByLetter and formatBirthday
    apple-contacts.test.ts    unit tests for normalizeKey, mergeContacts, deduplicateContacts, appleId extraction
```

## Key implementation details

- **JXA, not AppleScript**: `osascript -l JavaScript` via `child_process.execFile` — avoid `run-applescript`
- **Two-phase loading**: bulk fetch (`fetchAppleContacts`) returns id/name/company only (~0.4 s). Full detail (phones, emails, addresses, birthday, notes, photo) is fetched lazily via `fetchContactDetail` keyed on the selected contact
- **Contact photos**: JXA writes the image bytes to `/tmp/raycast-contact-<id>.jpg` and returns a `file://` URL stored in `photoUrl`
- **Label normalization**: Apple labels arrive as `_$!<Mobile>!$_`; `formatType()` strips the wrapper in both `ContactList` and `ContactActions`
- **Deduplication**: after bulk fetch, contacts are keyed by `normalizeKey(displayName)` (NFD accent-strip + lowercase). Same-key contacts are merged: first non-empty field wins; emails/phones take the richer side
- **Caching**: `useCachedPromise` caches list between sessions (instant re-open); detail is also cached per-contact object reference

## Performance

| Operation | Speed | Notes |
|-----------|-------|-------|
| Bulk list fetch | ~0.4 s | Single JXA call, bulk property access |
| Per-contact detail | ~0.1–0.3 s | `whose { id }` lookup, cached after first load |
| Subsequent opens | instant | `useCachedPromise` hits disk cache |

## Related rules

- `raycast-guidelines.mdc` — always-apply rule covering Raycast store submission requirements, naming conventions, UX patterns, and ActionPanel rules. Consult it before adding actions, changing `package.json` fields, or shipping any UX change.

## Protected files

**NEVER modify `assets/extension-icon.png`** unless the user explicitly asks to change the icon. Agents making code/feature changes must not touch this file.

## Dev workflow

```bash
npm run dev          # live-reload in Raycast
npm run build        # production build to dist/
npm run lint         # ESLint via @raycast/eslint-config
npm test             # vitest run (unit tests, no Raycast runtime needed)
npm run test:watch   # vitest watch mode
```

